title: S. Jersey Girls: S.J. girls: Carroll's OT winner lifts Holy Cross over Cinnaminson
text:
More coverage: Southeastern Pa. high school sports Williamstown 3, Winslow Township 2: Ashley Engler, Natalie Pantalone, and Lauren Wood scored for the sixth-seeded hosts. Winslow Township was seeded 11th.
Shawnee 6, Audubon 0: Christina Corbi and Sarah DeBerardinis had two goals apiece for the second-seeded hosts. Lexie Palladino added three assists. Audubon was seeded 15th. 
OLYMPIC CONFERENCE 
Bishop Eustace 3, Camden Catholic 0: Gabby Pietrangelo scored twice for the visitors. Dominique Marrone also scored and added two assists. 
BURLINGTON COUNTY LEAGUE 
Westampton Tech 3, Maple Shade 1: Izaryah Diggs, Angelina Murtaugh, and NazJahna Silvera scored for the home team. Alyson Harris made eight saves. 
Bordentown 4, Pemberton 2: Annette Ditolvo and Morgan Papp both scored twice for the visitors. 
Riverside, 4, Florence 0: Chelsea Jo Horta scored twice for the home team. Megan Crammer and Kenzee Hudson also scored. 
COLONIAL CONFERENCE 
Gateway 3, Overbrook 1: Gabby Franklin scored twice for the home team. Gianna Marley also scored. 
Haddon Township 5, Woodbury 0: Amanda Fox scored twice for the home team. Jamie Cutrera, Lauren Fletcher and Raylyn Straubmuller also scored. FIELD HOCKEY 
COLONIAL CONFERENCE 
Haddon Heights 4, Paulsboro 3, OT: Claudia Bowman scored twice in the home team's victory. 
Audubon 4, Sterling 1: Haleigh Atchinson scored twice for the hosts. Gabby Bobo and Kaci Draves also scored. 
OLYMPIC CONFERENCE 
Washington Township 3, Shawnee 2, OT: Iris Schuck scored twice in the visitors' overtime win. Jenna Patrone also tallied a goal.
